## Time Complexity

- Creating the preferred providers lookup: O(P) where P is the number of preferred providers

- Creating the provider-to-networks map: O(A) where A is the number of available providers

- Calculating coverage for all plans: O(I * N * P) where I is the number of insurance plans, N is the average number of networks per plan, and P is the number of preferred providers

- Sorting the plans: O(I log I) where I is the number of insurance plans

Overall time complexity: O(P + A + I * N * P + I log I)

In the worst case, this would be O(I * N * P) assuming I * N * P > I log I, which is typically the case for large datasets.

## Space Complexity

- Preferred providers lookup: O(P)

- Provider-to-networks map: O(A)

- Coverage scores: O(I)

Overall space complexity: O(P + A + I)

